description:
&lt;p&gt;The Orthopaedic Unit at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals is looking to recruit 2 Ward Assistants to support the Ward Manager on Wards Huntsman 2, 6 and 7 at the Northern General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a key role that provides confidential administrative support to the Ward Manager and Ward Co-ordinators releasing time so that they can lead and manage their nursing and support staff to ensure the delivery of high quality patient care in their clinical inpatient areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supporting the ward nursing team by working with various teams across the Trust and external to the hospital to ensure that all patients are discharged safely and effectively. You will also support the Ward Manager with administrative tasks related to staff management and clinical care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report directly to the nurse in charge but will have key relationships with the Ward Clerk, nursing team and clinical team looking after each patient&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this position you should have proven experience on a ward and be able to demonstrate that you can work independently and use your initiative to prioritise and complete conflicting demands in a timely and effective manner. You will be able to work flexibly to include weekend and evening working and work your working week over 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills and team working are essential for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Denise Wall (Sister , Huntsman 7) &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tel: 01142714108&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Marc Bagshaw (Charge Nurse , Huntsman 6)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tel: 01142714106&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Paul Steele (Charge Nurse, Huntsman 2)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tel: 01142714102&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the recruitment process at application stage, Sheffield Teaching Hospitals will assess applicants’ individual values and behaviours to ensure that these behaviours align with our PROUD values: Patient First, Respectful, Ownership, Unity and Deliver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are what help to make us different and ‘a Brilliant Place to Work’. We expect all our employees to share our values and demonstrate them in every aspect of their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake an online values assessment at application stage and the results of this assessment will be used as part of the on-going selection process to assess your suitability for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The deadline for completing the online assessment is midnight 18/11/2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The link to the assessment can be found below, the address can be copied and pasted into a search engine e.g. google:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; login.talentqgroup.com/Login/SelfService/KZSJCQRLPX&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any queries, require any assistance to complete this assessment or have already completed it within the past 12 months, please contact the Trust Recruitment Team at &lt;strong&gt;sth.centralrecruitment@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
